.UPDATE...
Issued at 844 AM PDT Fri Mar 20 2026

A clear morning across the region, with the clear skies continuing
throughout the day. This morning`s 12Z (5 AM PDT) sounding at OAK
set another 850 mb temperature record at 23.4 C, a maximum
temperature record that is not reached again until the middle of
May. It follows that today is another day of extreme heat across
the region with a lot of daily temperature records, and possibly
some monthly records, under threat. For more details on the
expected conditions today, and the cooling trend this weekend, see
the previous discussion.

